<abstract><t>As DDoS attacks evolve rapidly in the aspect of volume and sophistication, cooperation among operators becomes very necessary because it will give us quicker and more sophisticated protection to cope with them.  This document describes possible mechanisms which implement the cooperative inter-domain DDoS protection by DOTS protocol.  The described data models are intended to cover intra- domain and inter-domain solutions.</t></abstract>

